    console.error('❌ CORS FAILED:', error.message);
    if (error.message.includes('CORS policy')) {
      console.error('❌ CORS configuration still needed');
    }
  })
```

### What We're Looking For:

**✅ SUCCESS (CORS Working):**
- You should see: `✅ CORS SUCCESS! Response status: 200`
- No "blocked by CORS policy" errors

**❌ FAILURE (CORS Not Working):**
- You'll see: `❌ CORS FAILED: ... blocked by CORS policy`
- Red error message about Access-Control-Allow-Origin

---

Please run this test and tell me what you see in the console! This will immediately show us if your CORS configuration is working.

